I put out a little over $500 for a Lincoln and gas tank, conversion kit,
full tank of gas, large roll of wire.  (get large bottle of gas)  add in a
little over $150 for a self dimming mask.

and I was on the road, used up about a tank of gas before I was doing a
reasonable weld.  start where it won't be seen

> to be scoffed at the flux core wire is really nice for welding outside where
> your gas can be blown away but generally speaking it is better to pop
> for a MIG where you can run gas and still run the flux core wire if you

I got a large cardboard box and reversed it and use it as a shield to
protect from wind and accidental viewing by locals

> need to.  Century, Lincoln, Hobart, all have cheapy MIG welders down
> to as low as $350-400, they are all about the same in this price range, things
